olive oil
1 packet Beef Rump
1 tomato
1 cucumber
2 radish
½ lemon
1 packet garlic aioli
1 packet sriracha
1 packet sweet chilli sauce
1 bag salad leaves
1 packet roasted peanuts
1 packet Crispy Shallots
1 packet ponzu sauce
1 bag coriander & mint

• Place beef between two sheets of baking paper. Pound with rolling pin until slightly flattened (this ensures it’s extra tender!)
• Heat olive oil in frying pan over high heat. Season beef
• Cook beef for 5-6 mins or until cooked to your liking
• Transfer to a plate to rest

• Roughly chop tomato and cucumber
• Trim and thinly slice radish
• Cut lemon into wedges
• In a bowl, combine garlic aioli and sriracha

• In a second bowl, combine ponzu, sweet chilli, salad leaves, tomato, cucumber, radish, peanuts and torn coriander and mint
• Add a drizzle of oil, season and toss
• Slice steak
• Divide steak and salad between plates. Top with sriracha aioli and crispy shallots
• Serve with lemon wedges